spring-rest-demo

1. Open DemoAppConfig class and look for annotations.
2. Open MySpringDispatcherServletInitializer class and look for Parent class.
This is the configuration part to make the project spring readable.

3. Open DemoRestController and make it get hit using postman.
Use http://localhost:8180/spring-rest-demo/test/hello.

Debug is supported.

Open StudentController
4. Make a hit to http://localhost:8180/spring-rest-demo/api/student
and to http://localhost:8180/spring-rest-demo/api/student/1
5. Check for StudentNotFoundException.
6. Open StudentRestExceptionHandler, with annotation:- @ControllerAdvice.
7. Check how Error Message class:- StudentErrorResponse is used to provide message in response to user.



Links to read:-
1.https://github.com/FasterXML/jackson-annotations/wiki/Jackson-Annotations
2.https://www.freeformatter.com/mime-types-list.html
3.https://docs.spring.io/spring-boot/docs/current/reference/html/application-properties.html